1
00:00:06,741 --> 00:00:09,981
Akhirnya kami menemukanmu,
Pendekar Pedang Hitam!

2
00:00:13,441 --> 00:00:14,491
Hei, lihat.

3
00:00:14,801 --> 00:00:16,811
Apa itu pedang?

4
00:00:16,811 --> 00:00:17,981
Tidak mungkin...

5
00:00:17,981 --> 00:00:19,991
Tidak ada yang sanggup
memegang pedang itu!

6
00:00:21,081 --> 00:00:22,491
Laki-laki ini adalah

7
00:00:23,521 --> 00:00:25,001
Rajawali Kegelapan.

8
00:00:25,571 --> 00:00:28,951
{We are the Holy See's Holy Iron Chain Knights.}Kami adalah Takhta Suci
Kesatria Rantai Besi Kudus.

9
00:00:28,951 --> 00:00:33,011
{We have made haste, by order of the Miracle Certification Bureau,}Kami tengah buru-buru,
atas perintah Badan Sertifikasi Ghaib,

10
00:00:33,011 --> 00:00:34,181
{to take you to the Holy See.}untuk membawamu ke Takhta Suci.

11
00:00:34,181 --> 00:00:37,011
{You will not be harmed if you lay down your sword and surrender.}Kau takkan terluka apabila membuang pedangmu dan menyerah dengan baik-baik.

12
00:00:37,011 --> 00:00:41,181
{If not, we swear upon God
that you will be captured!}Kalau tidak, kami bersumpah atas nama Tuhan, kami akan menangkapmu!

13
00:00:41,181 --> 00:00:43,971
{I don't recall doing anything that'd
make a priest arrest me.}Aku tidak ingat apapun mengapa
pendeta ingin menangkapku.

14
00:00:43,971 --> 00:00:45,611
Sungguh tidak ada perasaan...

15
00:00:45,611 --> 00:00:47,301
Darah dari mana itu?

16
00:00:47,301 --> 00:00:48,501
Selagi kami melacakmu,

17
00:00:48,501 --> 00:00:52,271
{we saw the bodies of a monk,
his daughter, and countless others.}kami melihat mayat biarawan,
putrinya, dan masih banyak lagi.

18
00:00:53,981 --> 00:00:55,981
Guts...

19
00:00:54,781 --> 00:00:56,191
Waktu ngobrolnya sudah selesai!

20
00:00:56,621 --> 00:00:58,281
Inilah kehendak Tuhan!

21
00:00:58,711 --> 00:01:00,701
Pasukan, tangkap Pendekar Pedang Hitam!

22
00:01:06,971 --> 00:01:08,131
Kelihatannya gawat!

23
00:01:08,131 --> 00:01:10,131
Apa yang akan kau lakukan?

24
00:01:18,671 --> 00:01:22,141
Kesatria Rantai Besi Kudus

25
00:02:49,751 --> 00:02:51,891
Dengar, aku akan membuat celah.

26
00:02:51,891 --> 00:02:53,741
Saat itu, larilah ke hutan.

27
00:02:55,051 --> 00:02:56,061
Tapi...

28
00:02:56,061 --> 00:02:57,811
Jangan salah sangka!

29
00:02:57,811 --> 00:03:01,001
{Do you really want to die like this,
in the middle of nowhere?}Apa kau serius ingin mati
di tempat antah berantah ini?

30
00:03:02,381 --> 00:03:04,661
{A good blade should rest in a scabbard.}Pedang yang bagus harusnya tetap
bersemayam dalam sarungnya.

31
00:03:05,781 --> 00:03:08,741
{You should return to the master of your sword!}Harusnya kau kembali pada tuan pedangmu!

32
00:03:15,851 --> 00:03:17,021
Kenapa dia?

33
00:03:17,021 --> 00:03:18,341
Dia sama sekali tidak bisa
menggunakan pedangnya?

34
00:03:18,341 --> 00:03:19,461
Guts!

35
00:03:20,091 --> 00:03:21,211
{I can't get a good grip.}Aku tak bisa mengendalikannya!

36
00:03:21,211 --> 00:03:22,321
Bagus!

37
00:03:22,321 --> 00:03:23,721
Serang dia!

38
00:03:24,721 --> 00:03:25,801
Bodoh, jangan bunuh dia!

39
00:03:25,801 --> 00:03:26,811
D-Dia cepat...

40
00:03:26,811 --> 00:03:28,641
Hentikan, bisa-bisa kau membunuhnya.

41
00:03:34,861 --> 00:03:36,261
Tangan palsunya! Perhatikan tangannya!

42
00:03:36,261 --> 00:03:37,701
Tenang! Jangan terlalu membabi-buta!

43
00:03:37,701 --> 00:03:39,561
Kepung dia! Hentikan pergerakannya!

44
00:03:41,841 --> 00:03:43,141
Kita akan saling mengenai satu sama lain...

45
00:03:43,531 --> 00:03:45,531
Tidak!

46
00:03:44,091 --> 00:03:46,001
Bodoh! Kita tak boleh membunuhnya!

47
00:03:55,021 --> 00:03:56,421
Kalian semua menyedihkan...

48
00:03:56,421 --> 00:03:58,921
Kenapa satu buronan saja membuat
kalian berantakan begitu?

49
00:03:59,181 --> 00:04:00,851
Kau tak bisa menyalahkan mereka.

50
00:04:00,851 --> 00:04:03,751
Kesatria Rantai Besi Kudus juga dikenal sebagai "Ksatria Manja,"

51
00:04:03,751 --> 00:04:06,781
dipenuhi ahli waris yang dimanjakan oleh kebangsawan mereka yang ingin aman.

52
00:04:06,781 --> 00:04:09,761
Mereka berada di sini karena gengsi dan keamanan tingkatan kedudukan.

53
00:04:09,831 --> 00:04:12,951
{Most have never fought in a real battle.}Kebanyakan dari mereka tidak pernah bertarung di pertempuran sungguhan.

54
00:04:12,951 --> 00:04:14,351
Terima kasih atas ceramahnya.

55
00:04:14,351 --> 00:04:17,171
Mengapa Anda di sini, Sir Serpico?

56
00:04:17,171 --> 00:04:18,291
Oh, jangan begitu...

57
00:04:18,291 --> 00:04:19,751
Padahal sendirinya sudah tahu.

58
00:04:19,751 --> 00:04:22,991
Aku menjadi perwira perang
karena benci melihat darah—

59
00:04:30,641 --> 00:04:32,571
{Good... Now! Secure him!}Bagus... Sekarang! Amankan dia!

60
00:04:32,571 --> 00:04:33,801
Gawat.

61
00:04:54,521 --> 00:04:56,581
Inilah Pendekar Pedang Hitam...

62
00:04:56,581 --> 00:05:00,001
Kejahatannya sudah jelas.

63
00:05:00,541 --> 00:05:02,721
{He is the one written of in Revelations.}Dialah yang tertulis dalam Nubuat.

64
00:05:03,061 --> 00:05:04,281
Nona Farnese...

65
00:05:04,691 --> 00:05:06,401
Seperti yang Serpico nyatakan,

66
00:05:06,401 --> 00:05:09,471
{given our troops' combat inexperience,
we face mounting casualties}mengingat tidak adanya pengalaman tempur pasukan kita, kita menghadapi korban yang menggunung

67
00:05:09,471 --> 00:05:11,661
{if we seek to overwhelm him with numbers.}kalau kita terlalu menghadapi dia dengan jumlah.

68
00:05:12,001 --> 00:05:15,291
Saya ingin Anda mengizinkan saya, Azan, mengambil alih tugas ini!

69
00:05:21,951 --> 00:05:23,221
Mundur, mundur!

70
00:05:23,221 --> 00:05:24,421
Mundur!

71
00:05:24,891 --> 00:05:26,891
Wakil komandan...

72
00:05:25,621 --> 00:05:27,621
Sir Azan!

73
00:05:26,381 --> 00:05:29,471
Aku Azan, Wakil Komandan
Ksatria Rantai Besi Kudus!

74
00:05:30,461 --> 00:05:33,181
Kelihatannya orang yang
hebat mulai muncul!

75
00:05:33,641 --> 00:05:34,921
Tongkat Besi Iblis Azan?

76
00:05:34,921 --> 00:05:36,201
Aku sudah dengar tentangmu.

77
00:05:36,201 --> 00:05:39,221
Kalau tidak salah, kau juga disebut sebagai Ksatria Jembatan.

78
00:05:39,221 --> 00:05:41,221
Oh?

79
00:05:40,451 --> 00:05:42,361
Kau kenal orang ini, Guts?

80
00:05:42,801 --> 00:05:47,311
Ada cerita bahwa seorang kakek yang terluka berdiri di sebuah jembatan sempit.

81
00:05:47,311 --> 00:05:49,761
Ksatria Jembatan adalah seorang pria yang sukar dimengerti,

82
00:05:49,761 --> 00:05:52,781
{who refused to let an army of a hundred mounted men pass}yang tidak mengizinkan ratusan pasukan melintas

83
00:05:52,781 --> 00:05:54,661
{because he was protecting that guy.}karena dia melindungi orang itu.

84
00:05:54,661 --> 00:05:57,031
Itu cerita lama.

85
00:05:57,031 --> 00:06:01,921
{People laughed and said he could've ended it
by carrying the old man to the other side.}Orang-orang tertawa dan dikatakan dia akhirnya mampu membawa kakek itu ke sisi seberang.

86
00:06:01,921 --> 00:06:05,901
Seorang ksatria memiliki tugas untuk
menegakkan kode etiknya sebagai ksatria!

87
00:06:05,901 --> 00:06:07,911
{My circumstances led to being a cleric knight.}Keadaanku menuntunku untuk menjadi ksatria religius!

88
00:06:07,911 --> 00:06:09,821
{In any event, I have named myself.}Yang jelas, aku memiliki nama sendiri.

89
00:06:09,821 --> 00:06:12,181
Kalau kau ksatria, rasa kehormatan menuntutmu memberi jawaban!

90
00:06:12,181 --> 00:06:13,871
Aku bukan ksatria...

91
00:06:13,871 --> 00:06:15,871
Aku Guts.

92
00:06:14,851 --> 00:06:16,681
Cuma "Guts," Kek.

93
00:06:16,681 --> 00:06:18,661
Baiklah, Guts...

94
00:06:18,661 --> 00:06:19,691
Persiapkan dirimu!

95
00:06:19,691 --> 00:06:21,271
Dia itu ketinggalan zaman sekali.

96
00:06:21,271 --> 00:06:24,401
{Prepare to break at least one or two bones!}Bersiaplah hancur setidaknya
satu atau dua tulangmu!

97
00:06:28,721 --> 00:06:30,861
Satu atau dua tulang, ya?

98
00:06:31,531 --> 00:06:33,621
Aku tidak bisa terus
menghindar dengan kaki pincang.

99
00:06:38,431 --> 00:06:41,681
Dan kakek itu bukanlah orang bodoh yang hanya mengandalkan kekuatan besarnya.

100
00:06:44,051 --> 00:06:46,001
{You nimble trickster!}Kau penipu yang gesit!

101
00:06:46,501 --> 00:06:48,211
Orang barbar!

102
00:06:51,971 --> 00:06:53,221
{Vice-commander Azan!}Wakil komandan Azan!

103
00:06:56,731 --> 00:06:57,801
{I would commend you.}Aku memujimu.

104
00:06:57,801 --> 00:07:02,311
{But given your lack of offense,
your execution lacks finesse.}Tapi dengan seranganmu yang kurang, eksekusimu kurang mahir.

105
00:07:02,311 --> 00:07:04,131
{Your swordsmanship
affirmed its battle-testing.}Kemampuan berpedangmu kurang baik.

106
00:07:04,131 --> 00:07:06,281
{I'll admit it thrilled me,
hearkening to my own past.}Itu membuatku senang, membuatku mengingat masa laluku.

107
00:07:06,281 --> 00:07:09,631
{I must apply myself to the order
with greater diligence,}Aku harus memposisikan diriku untuk mengikuti perintah dengan baik,

108
00:07:09,631 --> 00:07:11,701
{to mend my foolish ways.}untuk memperbaiki kesalahanku.

109
00:07:12,191 --> 00:07:13,361
{Shit...}Sial...

110
00:07:13,361 --> 00:07:15,451
Aku hampir tidak bisa merasakan kakiku lagi.

111
00:07:15,451 --> 00:07:16,561
{What should I do?}Apa yang harus kulakukan?

112
00:07:20,651 --> 00:07:21,901
{A frontal attack?}Serangan langsung?

113
00:07:21,901 --> 00:07:22,981
{Commendable resolve!}Usaha yang patut dihargai.

114
00:07:25,401 --> 00:07:27,401
{What?}Apa?

115
00:07:26,401 --> 00:07:27,751
Dia berhasil lolos!

116
00:07:28,311 --> 00:07:29,431
{Lady Farnese!}Nona Farnese!

117
00:07:54,301 --> 00:07:57,491
{I was the one who put him down?}Aku yang telah mengalahkannya?

118
00:07:57,841 --> 00:07:59,651
{Well done, Lady Farnese.}Bagus, Nona Farnese.

119
00:07:59,651 --> 00:08:01,581
Komandan kami memang hebat!

120
00:08:01,581 --> 00:08:03,371
{Hey, you! Get up!}Hei, kau! Bangun!

121
00:08:03,371 --> 00:08:04,931
{Wait, is he dead?}Jangan-jangan, apa dia mati?

122
00:08:04,931 --> 00:08:07,081
{He's unconscious. He seems to be asleep.}Pingsan... Tidak, sepertinya dia tertidur.

123
00:08:07,081 --> 00:08:09,431
Oh, Tonio!

124
00:08:09,431 --> 00:08:10,841
{He was a good man...}Padahal dia pria yang baik...

125
00:08:12,071 --> 00:08:15,131
{Lady Farnese, please order a retreat.}Nona Farnese, tolong perintahkan kami mundur.

126
00:08:16,421 --> 00:08:20,561
{Lady Farnese, was this the
first blood you've drawn?}Nona Farnese, apa ini darah pertama yang Anda tumpahkan?

127
00:08:20,961 --> 00:08:24,341
{As one who wields a sword,
you mustn't fear it.}Sebagai orang yang menggunakan pedang, Anda tak perlu takut.

128
00:08:24,341 --> 00:08:27,681
{But always remember
the weight of a life taken,}Tapi selalu ingat beratnya nyawa yang Anda tanggung,

129
00:08:27,681 --> 00:08:30,571
{so long as you have men under your command.}selama Anda memiliki orang yang bisa diperintah.

130
00:08:36,161 --> 00:08:37,411
{What's this?}Apa ini?

131
00:08:41,481 --> 00:08:42,531
{Very well!}Baiklah!

132
00:08:42,531 --> 00:08:43,911
{All troops, retreat!}Semua pasukan, mundur!

133
00:08:53,771 --> 00:08:55,841
{Hey, are you alive?}Hei, apa kau masih hidup?

134
00:08:56,201 --> 00:08:58,171
{Yeah, somehow.}Yah, sepertinya.

135
00:08:59,531 --> 00:09:03,461
{Well, you're a hard one to kill.}Ya ampun, kau memang susah untuk dibunuh.

136
00:09:08,551 --> 00:09:09,651
Ayo.

137
00:09:23,111 --> 00:09:24,571
{Good work.}Kerja bagus.

138
00:09:24,951 --> 00:09:29,491
{On the battlefield, a common soldier's life
is worth less than a single silver coin.}Di medan perang, nyawa tentara biasa tidak lebih dari sekadar satu koin silver.

139
00:09:30,951 --> 00:09:33,871
{In this day and age, most people are}Di zaman sekarang ini, kebanyakan orang

140
00:09:33,871 --> 00:09:36,481
{abused by royalty and the nobility.}dimanfaatkan oleh kesetiaan dan kebangsawanan.

141
00:09:37,041 --> 00:09:41,301
{Well, not that even kings can
live as they please.}Yah, bukan berarti para raja tak
boleh hidup sesuka mereka.

142
00:09:42,151 --> 00:09:45,061
{Everyone is merely swept along by the tide.}Semua orang hanya mengikuti gelombang.

143
00:09:45,491 --> 00:09:47,511
{The tide known as fate.}Gelombang yang dikenal sebagai takdir.

144
00:09:47,511 --> 00:09:48,841
{And their lives spent,}Dan mereka menghabiskan hidup mereka,

145
00:09:49,611 --> 00:09:51,501
{they vanish into its depths.}menghilang ke dalamnya.

146
00:09:51,501 --> 00:09:54,131
{They die before learning who they truly are.}Mereka mati sebelum mengetahui siapa diri mereka sebenarnya.

147
00:09:55,821 --> 00:09:59,391
{Some, regardless of rank or station,
are born as key individuals,}Beberapa orang, tak peduli kelas atau kedudukan, telah lahir sebagai kunci individual,

148
00:09:59,391 --> 00:10:00,991
{who will shape this world.}yang akan membentuk dunia ini.

149
00:10:02,211 --> 00:10:04,781
{They are the true privileged class.}Merekalah kelas istimewa yang sebenarnya.

150
00:10:05,931 --> 00:10:10,251
{I want to know who I am in this world.}Aku ingin tahu siapa diriku di dunia ini.

151
00:10:10,251 --> 00:10:11,911
{What I am capable of,}Apa yang kubisa,

152
00:10:11,911 --> 00:10:13,811
{and what I am meant to do.}dan apa yang ingin kulakukan.

153
00:10:15,751 --> 00:10:17,171
{How strange.}Aneh sekali.

154
00:10:17,171 --> 00:10:20,221
{I've never spoken to anyone about this before.}Aku tak pernah membicarakan ini ke seseorang.

155
00:10:20,841 --> 00:10:22,041
<i>{At that moment,}Waktu itu,</i>

156
00:10:22,041 --> 00:10:27,771
<i>{the man appeared to me as something
beautiful, noble, and absolute.}laki-laki itu muncul di depanku sebagai sesuatu yang cantik, mulia, dan mutlak.</i>

157
00:11:08,881 --> 00:11:10,711
{We have brought the Black Swordsman.}Kami telah membawa Pendekar Pedang Hitam.

158
00:11:10,711 --> 00:11:12,711
{Enter.}Masuk.

159
00:11:11,381 --> 00:11:13,381
{Yes, my lady.}Iya, Nona.

160
00:11:14,441 --> 00:11:16,441
{Well done.}Bagus.

161
00:11:15,411 --> 00:11:19,051
{After you bind him to the post,
you are free to go.}Sesudah kau mengikatnya di tiang, kau boleh pergi.

162
00:11:19,051 --> 00:11:20,281
{But that would—}Tapi itu akan—

163
00:11:20,281 --> 00:11:22,281
{No need for concern.}Tak perlu khawatir.

164
00:11:21,261 --> 00:11:24,451
{With those gigantic shackles,
what harm could he possibly do?}Dengan belenggu-belenggu yang besar itu, apa yang bisa dia lakukan?

165
00:11:24,801 --> 00:11:26,531
{We shall inform the vice-commander, then.}Kalau begitu, kami akan memberitahu wakil komandan.

166
00:11:26,531 --> 00:11:28,531
{That won't be necessary.}Itu tidak perlu.

167
00:11:27,531 --> 00:11:29,531
{But...}Tapi...

168
00:11:28,331 --> 00:11:33,751
{Further, instruct the guards to leave
this tent until I order otherwise.}Selanjutnya, perintahkan para penjaga untuk meninggalkan tenda ini sampai aku perintahkan lagi.

169
00:11:33,751 --> 00:11:36,001
{But if something should happen...}Tapi kalau terjadi sesuatu...

170
00:11:36,001 --> 00:11:37,571
{We should inform the vice-commander.}Kami harus memberitahu wakil komandan.

171
00:11:37,571 --> 00:11:39,431
{What is your name and rank?}Siapa namamu dan apa kelasmu?

172
00:11:40,081 --> 00:11:42,461
{You dare say you cannot follow my order}Kau berani tidak mengikuti perintahku

173
00:11:42,461 --> 00:11:44,861
{unless the vice-commander tells you to?!}kecuali wakil komandan yang menyuruhmu?!

174
00:11:44,861 --> 00:11:49,151
{Tell me, who is the Supreme Commander
of the Holy Iron Chain Knights?}Beritahu aku, siapa Komandan tertinggi di Kesatria Rantai Besi Kudus?

175
00:11:49,151 --> 00:11:51,441
Anda yang tertinggi, Komandan Farnese!

176
00:11:51,841 --> 00:11:54,731
Maaf atas ketidaksopanan saya!

177
00:11:54,731 --> 00:11:56,861
{As long as you bear this in mind. Leave.}Tidak apa-apa selama kau mengingatnya. Pergilah.

178
00:11:56,861 --> 00:11:58,861
Baik!

179
00:12:00,881 --> 00:12:02,451
{Black Swordsman...}Pendekar Pedang Hitam...

180
00:12:02,901 --> 00:12:05,411
{Or should I say... Guts, was it?}Atau harus kupanggil... Guts, bukan?

181
00:12:05,411 --> 00:12:08,351
{Before we deliver you to the Holy See,}Sebelum kami mengantarmu ke Takhta Suci,

182
00:12:08,351 --> 00:12:11,601
{it falls to me, as one of the grand
tribunal's junior members,}sebagai salah satu anggota baru pengadilan agung,

183
00:12:11,601 --> 00:12:14,131
{to ask you a few simple questions.}aku akan memberimu beberapa pertanyaan.

184
00:12:15,891 --> 00:12:17,711
{Why do you laugh, cur?!}Apa yang kau tertawakan, bajingan?!

185
00:12:18,041 --> 00:12:21,401
{Oh, I was just thinking that
I have the worst luck}Oh, aku hanya berpikir kalau aku kurang beruntung

186
00:12:21,401 --> 00:12:23,891
{with God and things of that ilk.}dengan Tuhan dan hal semacam itu.

187
00:12:24,201 --> 00:12:28,101
{Blasphemy. I shan't allow you
to blaspheme a second time.}Penistaan Tuhan. Aku takkan membiarkanmu melakukannya lagi.

188
00:12:30,211 --> 00:12:31,601
{The Band of the Hawk.}Sekumpulan Rajawali.

189
00:12:33,581 --> 00:12:36,021
{A band of mercenaries, hired by Midland.}Sekumpulan tentara bayaran,
yang dipekerjakan oleh Midland.

190
00:12:36,401 --> 00:12:37,821
{The Band of the Hawk.}Sekumpulan Rajawali.

191
00:12:39,951 --> 00:12:42,631
{An elite military force that
won countless victories,}Pasukan militer elit yang banyak memperoleh kemenangan,

192
00:12:42,631 --> 00:12:44,811
{their military prowess
was said to be peerless.}kekuatan militer mereka katanya tak ada tandingannya.

193
00:12:44,811 --> 00:12:48,291
{But they plotted treason against the royal
family, becoming wanted fugitives.}Tapi mereka berencana mengkhianati keluarga kerajaan, lalu menjadi buronan.

194
00:12:53,731 --> 00:12:57,641
{However, the entire company
